An authorized control level event occurs when:
an insurer files an RBC report that indicates that the insurer has total adjusted capital that is:
greater than or equal to its mandatory control level RBC; and
less than its authorized control level RBC;
the Commissioner notifies the insurer of an adjusted RBC report that indicates an event under item (1) of this subsection;
if an insurer requests a hearing to challenge an adjusted RBC report that indicates the event under item (1) of this subsection, the Commissioner notifies the insurer that the Commissioner, after a hearing, has rejected the insurer's challenge;
the insurer fails to respond to a corrective order in a manner satisfactory to the Commissioner; or
if an insurer has requested a hearing to challenge a corrective order issued by the Commissioner:
the Commissioner notifies the insurer that the Commissioner, after a hearing, has rejected the insurer's challenge or modified the corrective order; and
the insurer fails to respond, in a manner satisfactory to the Commissioner, to the sustained or modified corrective order.
